# Prime Candidates 1,000,000–1,002,000 — Raw vs Adjusted OMNIA Results

Status: million-range validation run  
Scope: 800 candidates in the interval 1,000,000–1,002,000  
Method: raw OMNIA vs adjusted OMNIA with regularity penalty  
Interpretation level: high-scale generalization test of the correction

---

## Goal

This run was designed to test whether the regularity correction remains effective when prime density drops and structured composite traps become more dangerous.

The tested setup was:

```text
Ω_adjusted = Ω_raw - λ * regularity_penalty_norm

with:

λ = 0.03


This value had already emerged as the best balanced setting in the previous lambda sweep.


